{"questionId":"3395495","questionHtml":"<p>A thermodynamic cycle consisting of an adiabatic, isovolumetric and isothermal processes is shown.</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/6a6cc9a9531129be7daba1cbd4527da19dd97214.png\"></p>\n<p>Which of the following correctly identifies the processes of the cycle?</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<table style=\"width:494px;\" border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width:35px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width:125px;text-align:center;\"><strong>Adiabatic</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width:156.406px;text-align:center;\"><strong>Isovolumetric</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width:183.594px;text-align:center;\"><strong>Isothermal</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width:35px;\">&nbsp;A.</td>\n<td style=\"width:125px;text-align:center;\">X→Y</td>\n<td style=\"width:156.406px;text-align:center;\">Y→Z</td>\n<td style=\"width:183.594px;text-align:center;\">Z→X</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width:35px;\">&nbsp;B.</td>\n<td style=\"width:125px;text-align:center;\">Z→X</td>\n<td style=\"width:156.406px;text-align:center;\">X→Y</td>\n<td style=\"width:183.594px;text-align:center;\">Y→Z</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width:35px;\">&nbsp;C.</td>\n<td style=\"width:125px;text-align:center;\">Z→X</td>\n<td style=\"width:156.406px;text-align:center;\">Y→Z</td>\n<td style=\"width:183.594px;text-align:center;\">X→Y</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width:35px;\">&nbsp;D.</td>\n<td style=\"width:125px;text-align:center;\">Y→Z</td>\n<td style=\"width:156.406px;text-align:center;\">Z→X</td>\n<td style=\"width:183.594px;text-align:center;\">X→Y</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>","markschemeHtml":"<p>C</p>","meta":{"questionId":"3395495","referenceCode":"EXE.1A.HL.TZ0.17","subjectId":"59-dp-physics-first-assessment-2025","title":"A thermodynamic cycle consisting of an adiabatic, isovolumetric and isothermal processes is shown. Which of the following correctly identifies the processes of the cycle? Adiabatic","paper":"1A","level":"HL","questionNumber":"17","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["B. The particulate nature of matter","B. The particulate nature of matter","B.4 Thermodynamics"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}